address: The main entrance of Changdeokgung Palace
description: Changdeokgung Dunhwamun is the main gate of Changdeokgung Palace. Designated as Treasure No. 383 of the Republic of Korea. It was built in the 12th year of Emperor Taizong (1412). After the Imjin Japanese Rebellion, it was used as the main gate of Gyeongbokgung Palace instead of Gwanghwamun Gate. After the restoration of Gyeongbokgung Palace in Gojong 2 years, it was used again as the main gate of Ligung Palace (Changdeokgung Palace).
